# Pricing & Financial Policy

## Background pricing engine

Runs after technical spec is saved. Technician never sees prices during spec entry.

## Quote cost basis — Highest Purchase Price (not WAC)

For patient quotes and pending pricing:

```
line_cost = qty × highest_registered_purchase_price(item)
quote_total = Σ line_cost + configured margin
```

WAC is for **inventory valuation and financial reports only** — not for civilian quote building.

## Civilian financial flow

1. `PricingRequest` → admin approval → `Quote` with QR
2. Contract entity approval (OCR/scan) unlocks manufacturing
3. On delivery: post receivable to `ContractCompany` / debt ledger
4. Credit notes for partial/full rejection after delivery (`CreditNote`)

## Military financial flow

- Calculate full cost silently on pricing event
- No quote, no payment gate, no patient billing
- On delivery: accumulate cost to **sovereign / military debt** bucket for BI board 4

## Contract entities (`ContractCompany`)

- Civilian insurers, NGOs, etc. — normal AR/debt tracking
- Military sovereign entities — reporting-only debt, no payment demand

## BI financial metrics (board 4)

- Cumulative civilian cost by contract entity
- Aggregated military cost (sovereign)
- Net contract debts outstanding

Purchasing board (5): compare WAC vs highest purchase price per item for negotiation.
